<p>I'm using angular#1.4.2 and angular-ui-router#0.2.13. Every ui-sref attribute creates a watcher. I'm using the below syntax.</p>  <pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>data-ui-sref="p.messages.tab.id({tab: $state.params.tab, id: msg.id})" </code></pre>  <p>How to make ui-sref to bind only once?</p>  <h2>Update</h2>  <p>Install angular extension in chrome and check under Performance section of it. Every <strong>ui-sref with arguments</strong> on the page creates a watcher. I want to bind only once and don't want to create any watches on the ui-sref arguments expression. In the above example, <code>{tab: $state.params.tab, id: msg.id}</code> watch is created.</p>